N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 8 ยง 113.24 - Dismissal of appeal

State Regulations

The appeal board may, in its discretion and at any stage of
the proceedings, on its own motion or on the application of any party, dismiss
an appeal if the appeal has become moot or the parties have reached a mutually
agreeable settlement. Notes
